To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All records that contain any of the following keywords:
 “Claremont” 
@claremont.org
“True The Vote”
@truethevote.org
“Constitutional Sheriffs and Peace Officers Association” 
 “CSPOA”
@cspoa.org
“Catherine Engelbrecht”
“Gregg Phillips” 
“Richard Mack”
“Mike Lindell”
“Mark Lamb”
“Cause of America”
“Election integrity”
“Voter fraud”
“Election fraud”
“Drop box”
“Dropbox”
“Voting machine”
“Dominion”
“Non-citizen voting”
“Illegal voting”
“Illegals voting”
“Only Citizens Vote”

2. Receipts, confirmations and correspondence related to any and all lodging arrangements, transportation, including but not limited to air and ground transportation, meals, incidental expenses, and any other event-related expenses arranged, coordinated, sponsored, and/or paid for by any of the entities listed above.

3. Calendars, calendar invites, and other scheduling records for the Sheriff related to any and all events and meetings. 

The search for records requested above may be limited between January 1, 2024 through to the date of your final response. 

The search for records should include emails, attachments, both sent and received, scheduling records, text messages, mobile-phone-based/computer-based text communications including but not limited to Telegram, Signal, WhatsApp, materials received from postal mail, handouts, agendas, meeting packets and any other records containing the keywords and email domains in the request. 

Please note that the Sheriff and staff are acting in their official capacity when coordinating matters with outside entities, such as the CSPOA, that relate to official business. The search for records should also include all email accounts used to conduct official business, including personal email addresses such as a "gmail" or "yahoo" account.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Karen Goll.

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

File 65-HQ-64903, captioned "KOBCASE".

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records for all relevant names, individuals, agencies and companies. This is also to include any responsive records held in offsite locations, such as the Alexandria Records Center. Please include both investigatory and non-investigatory records in your search. If any potentially responsive records have been destroyed and/or transferred to NARA, then I request copies of the destruction or transfer slips as well as any other documentation relating to, mentioning or describing said transfer or destruction, to include but not be limited to confirmation that the Bureau has no other copies of said records. If previously released records are available, then I request a rolling release consisting of those records while additional records are located and processed for release.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Paul Galante

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: AB-481 Sub-Committee
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All writings associated with the Board of Supervisors AB-481 Sub-Committee. This should include all meeting schedules, agendas, minutes as well as all staff reports prepared for the sub-committee, all public or internal notices, requests for information and resulting responses, all external writings received by the committee and any other writings associated with the sub-committee not mentioned here.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Frank Shinneman

communications.subject: Minnesota Government Data Practices Act Request: Arrest Data Request
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Minnesota Government Data Practices Act, I hereby request the following records:

Crime data with arrest information for the City of Minneapolis, which should include at least the following details:

1. Case Number: Should correspond with the crime data available on the City Open Data Portal [https://opendata.minneapolismn.gov/datasets/cityoflakes::crime-data/about].
2. Arrest Information: Details of arrests made.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

bocar ba
